# Monorepo Boundaries

```
apps/website  ──┐
apps/backend  ──┼──→  packages/shared  ←── types, API contracts, constants
apps/bot      ──┘

haulbot-extension/  (separate repo — never imported by apps)
```

## Allowed

- Any app → `packages/shared`
- Backend → MongoDB, vault, analytics engine clients
- Website → backend via BFF `/api/v1/*` fetch only
- Bot → backend via service token HTTP only

## Forbidden

- `apps/website` importing `apps/backend/src/**`
- `apps/bot` importing backend repositories or DB clients directly
- Duplicating shared types in two apps — add to `packages/shared`
- Business logic in bot or extension that belongs in backend orchestration

## Extension repo

- Polls backend API; emits Load Telemetry via standard interface
- No Telegram, no Stripe, no MongoDB driver in extension code

Violations are caught by `fallow` boundary rules in `.fallowrc.json`.
